The paper discusses a method for parsing questions in order to retrieve answers from structured databases, which is a common problem in natural language processing and information retrieval. The paper also mentions reinforcement learning and policy gradient objectives, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases).
